#, no-wrap
msgid "Kernel Changes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:64
msgid ""
"The man:arcmsr[4] driver has been updated to version "
"1.20.00.28. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=256033[r256033]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:66
msgid ""
"The man:isci[4] driver is now loadable via "
"man:kldload[8]. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=256437[r256437] "
"(Sponsored by The FreeBSD Foundation)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:68
msgid ""
"System-level man:sysctl[8] values are now exposed to the system for the "
"man:ixgbe[4] "
"device. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=256759[r256759]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:70
msgid ""
"The man:mfi[4] driver has been updated to support MegaRAID Invader "
"controllers. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=256924[r256924]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:72
msgid ""
"A kernel panic triggered in `zfs_root()` after a failed rollback has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=257119[r257119]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:74
msgid ""
"A new man:sysctl[8], `debug.devfs_iosize_max_clamp` has been added which "
"enables and disables `SSIZE_MAX`-sized I/O requests on man:devfs[5] "
"files. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=257125[r257125] "
"(Sponsored by The FreeBSD Foundation)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:76
msgid ""
"A new man:sysctl[8], `kern.disallow_high_osrel`, has been added which "
"disables executing the images compiled on a userland with a higher major "
"version number than the major version number of the running "
"kernel. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=257126[r257126] "
"(Sponsored by The FreeBSD Foundation)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:78
msgid ""
"A kernel panic triggered by unmounting a busy man:zfs[8] filesystem has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=257253[r257253]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:80
msgid ""
"A deadlock triggered by powering off a USB device has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=257373[r257373]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:82
msgid ""
"The man:ichsmb[4] driver has been updated to support Intel Lynx Point PCH "
"SMBus "
"devices. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258214[r258214]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:84
msgid ""
"The man:ata[4] driver has been updated to support Coleto Creek "
"devices. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258215[r258215]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:86
msgid ""
"The man:ahci[4] driver has been updated to support the PCI-express solid "
"state drive in the Apple(R) MacBook Air (model "
"A1465). "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258217[r258217]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:88
msgid ""
"The man:sysctl[8] `vfs.zfs.arc_meta_limit` can now be changed at "
"runtime. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258635[r258635]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:90
msgid ""
"The man:mmap[2] system call has been updated to more optimally use "
"superpages and provide support for tweaking the alignment of virtual "
"mappings. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258870[r258870]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:92
msgid ""
"A workaround has been implemented in the man:bge[4] driver for hung "
"transmission on BCM5719 and BCM5720 "
"chipsets. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258962[r258962]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:94
msgid ""
"A kernel panic when listing sysctls on a system with `INVARIANTS` enabled "
"has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=259002[r259002]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:96
msgid ""
"A new man:sysctl[8], `kern.supported_archs` has been added, which will list "
"the `MACHINE_ARCH` values whose binaries can be run on the "
"system. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=259466[r259466]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:98
msgid ""
"Several problems that could trigger kernel panic on man:kldload[8] and "
"man:kldunload[8] have been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=259519[r259519] "
"(Sponsored by Spectra Logic)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:100
msgid ""
"A kernel panic triggered by some multi-threaded applications has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260082[r260082] "
"(Sponsored by The FreeBSD Foundation)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:102
msgid ""
"The man:runfw[4] firmware has been renamed from `runfw` to `run.fw` for "
"consistency with other firmware "
"files. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260134[r260134]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:104
msgid ""
"A new man:sysctl[8], `kern.panic_reboot_wait_time`, has been added. This "
"allows tuning the amount of time the system will wait before rebooting after "
"man:panic[9]. The `kern.panic_reboot_wait_time` value defaults to the kernel "
"configuration option, "
"`PANIC_REBOOT_WAIT_TIME`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260433[r260433]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:106
msgid ""
"Hardware Random Number Generators have been disabled by "
"default. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260644[r260644]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:108
msgid ""
"Support for GPS ports has been added to the man:uhso[4] "
"driver. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=261485[r261485]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:110
msgid ""
"A memory leak of compressed buffers has been fixed in "
"`l2arc_write_done()`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262116[r262116]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:112
msgid ""
"The man:netmap[4] framework has been updated to match the version in "
"`head/`, which includes netmap pipes, kqueue support, and enhanced VALE "
"switch "
"port. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262153[r262153]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:114
msgid ""
"A deadlock triggered by sending a mounted man:zfs[8] snapshot has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262175[r262175]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:116
msgid ""
"Support for SIIG X1 PCI-e has been added to "
"man:ppc[4]. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262231[r262231]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:118
msgid ""
"Support for the ext4 filesystem has been enabled, supporting read-only "
"mounts. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262564[r262564]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:120
msgid ""
"A kernel panic triggered by inserting a USB ethernet device on "
"VIMAGE-enabled systems has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262594[r262594]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:122
msgid ""
"TTM, a memory manager used by video drivers, has been "
"merged. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262988[r262988] "
"(Sponsored by The FreeBSD Foundation)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:124
msgid ""
"Support for `/sys/kernel/random/uuid` has been added to "
"man:linprocfs[5]. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263103[r263103]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:126
msgid ""
"A memory leak in the `zpool_in_use()` function has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263128[r263128]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:128
msgid ""
"The `extensible_dataset` man:zpool[8] feature has been added. See "
"man:zpool-features[7] for more "
"information. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263391[r263391]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:130
msgid ""
"A memory leak has been fixed in "
"`libzfs`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263408[r263408]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:132
msgid ""
"The man:vt[4] driver has been merged from "
"`head/`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263817,263818[r263817,263818] "
"(Sponsored by The FreeBSD Foundation)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:134
msgid ""
"The man:mpr[4] device has been added, providing support for LSI Fusion-MPT 3 "
"12Gb SCSI/SATA "
"controllers. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=265729[r265729] "
"(Sponsored by LSI, Spectra Logic)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:136
msgid ""
"A kernel bug that inhibited proper functionality of the `dev.cpu.0.freq` "
"man:sysctl[8] on Intel(R) processors with Turbo Boost ™ enabled has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=266167[r266167]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:138
msgid ""
"Support for man:xen[4] hardware-assisted virtualization, `XENHVM`, is now "
"available as a loadable module, "
"`xenhvm.ko`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=266269[r266269]"
msgstr ""

