#. type: Title ==
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "File Systems"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:193
msgid ""
"The man:zfs[8] filesystem has been updated to support the `bookmarks` "
"feature. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263410[r263410]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:195
#, no-wrap
msgid "Userland Changes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:198
msgid ""
"A new flag `-c`, has been added to man:pgrep[1] and man:pkill[1], which "
"restricts the process lookup to the specified login "
"class. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=256054[r256054]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:200
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The man:ddb[8] utility has been updated to add `show ioapic` and `show all       "
"ioapics`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=257496[r257496]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:202
msgid ""
"Setting `nmbcluster` values to their current value will now be ignored, "
"instead of failing with an "
"error. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258183[r258183]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:204
msgid ""
"The `/var/cache` directory is now created with mode `0755` instead of mode "
"`0750`, since this directory is used by many third-party applications, which "
"makes dropping group privileges "
"impossible. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258763[r258763]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:206
msgid ""
"The man:uname[1] utility has been updated to include the `-U` and `-K` "
"flags, which print the `__FreeBSD_version` for the running userland and "
"kernel, "
"respectively. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258818[r258818]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:208
msgid ""
"The man:fetch[3] library has been updated to support SNI (Server Name "
"Identification), allowing to use virtual hosts on "
"HTTPS. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=258844[r258844]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:210
msgid ""
"A segmentation fault and internal compiler error bug in man:gcc[1] triggered "
"by throwing a warning before parsing any tokens has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=259243[r259243]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:212
msgid ""
"Several updates to man:gcc[1] have been imported from "
"Google. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=259269,259406[r259269,259406] "
"(Contributed / provided by Google)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:214
msgid ""
"A byte-order bug in the Heimdal `gss_pseudo_random()` function which would "
"prevent interoperability with other Kerberos implementations has been "
"fixed. In particular, this would prevent interoperability with the MIT "
"implementation. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=259448[r259448]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:216
msgid ""
"The man:hastctl[8] utility has been updated to output the current queue "
"sizes. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260007[r260007]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:218
msgid ""
"The man:ps[1] utility will no longer truncate the `command` output "
"column. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260197[r260197]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:220
msgid ""
"The man:protect[1] command has been added, which allows exempting processes "
"from being killed when swap is "
"exhausted. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260208[r260208]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:222
msgid ""
"The man:gmirror[8] utility now prevents deactivating the last component of a "
"mirror. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260507[r260507]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:224
msgid ""
"A new man:gmirror[8] command, `gmirror destroy`, has been added, which will "
"destroy the man:geom[8] and erase the man:gmirror[8] "
"metadata. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260507[r260507]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:226
msgid ""
"The man:etcupdate[8] utility, a tool for managing updates to files in "
"`/etc`, has been merged from "
"`head/`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260650[r260650]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:228
msgid ""
"The man:find[1] utility has been updated to fix incorrect behavior with the "
"`-lname` and `-ilname` "
"flags. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260651[r260651]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:230
msgid ""
"The `hw.uart.console` is now always updated when the comconsole setup "
"changes. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260868,260869[r260868,260869]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:232
msgid ""
"The man:kldload[8] utility has been updated to display a message directing "
"to man:dmesg[8], instead of the cryptic message \"Exec format "
"error\". "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260909[r260909]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:234
msgid ""
"A bug that could trigger an infinite loop in KDE and X has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=261674[r261674]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:236
msgid ""
"The man:newsyslog[8] utility has been changed to use the size of the file, "
"instead of the blocks the file takes on the disk to match the behavior "
"documented in "
"man:newsyslog.conf[5]. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262076[r262076]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:238
msgid ""
"A bug in man:zdb[8] which would cause numeric parameters to a flag as being "
"treated as additional flags has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262105[r262105]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:240
msgid ""
"The man:pciconf[8] utility now has a `-V` flag, which lists information such "
"as serial numbers for each "
"device. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262134[r262134]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:242
msgid ""
"A bug that would allow creating a man:zfs[8] snapshot of an inconsistent "
"dataset has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262158[r262158]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:244
msgid ""
"Receiving a man:zfs[8] dataset with `zfs recv -F` now properly destroys any "
"snapshots that were created since the incremental source "
"snapshot. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=262160[r262160]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:246
msgid ""
"Installation from a read-only `.OBJDIR` has been "
"fixed. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263031[r263031]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:248
msgid ""
"A new shared library directory, `/usr/lib/private`, has been added for "
"internal-use shared "
"libraries. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263031[r263031]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:250
msgid ""
"A default `libmap32.conf` has been added, for 32-bit "
"applications. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263031[r263031]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:252
msgid ""
"The `libucl` library, a JSON-compatible configuration file parsing library, "
"has been "
"imported. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263032[r263032]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:254
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The man:pkg[7] package management utility has been syncronized with "
"`head/`. This implements binary package signature verification when "
"bootstrapping the system with `pkg       "
"bootstrap`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263038[r263038]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:256
msgid ""
"The system timezone data files have been updated to version "
"tzdata2014a. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263042[r263042]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:258
msgid ""
"The NetBSD man:make[1] utility, `bmake` has been imported for compatibility "
"with the FreeBSD Ports Collection. It is installed as `bmake`, and the "
"`make` remains the FreeBSD "
"version. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263212[r263212]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:260
msgid ""
"The man:fetch[3] library now supports `Last-Modified` timestamps which "
"return UTC instead of "
"GMT. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263326[r263326]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:262
msgid ""
"Aliases for the man:zfs[8] commands `list -t snap` and `snap` have been "
"added to match Oracle(R) Solaris "
"11. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263404[r263404]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:264
msgid ""
"A new flag, `-p`, has been added to the man:zfs[8] `list` command, providing "
"output in a parseable "
"form. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263406[r263406]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:266
msgid ""
"OpenPAM has been updated to Nummularia (20130907), which incorporates "
"several bug fixes and documentation improvements. The man:openpam_ttyconv[3] "
"library has been completely "
"rewritten. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263421[r263421]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:268
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The man:sh[1] command interpreter has been updated to expand assignments "
"after `export`, `local`, and `readonly` differently. As result of this "
"change, variable assignment such as `local       v=$1` will assign the first "
"positional parameter to `v`, even if `$1` contains spaces, and `local "
"w=~/myfile` will expand the tilde "
"(`~`). "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=264423[r264423]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:270
msgid ""
"The man:find[1] utility has been updated to implement "
"`-ignore_readdir_race`. Prior to this change, `-ignore_readdir_race` existed "
"as an option for GNU man:find[1] compatibility, and was ignored if "
"specified. A counter primary, `-noignore_readdir_race` now also exists, and "
"is the default "
"behavior. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=264699[r264699]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:272
msgid ""
"The man:ps[1] utility has been updated to include the `-J` flag, used to "
"filter output by matching man:ail[8] IDs and names. Additionally, argument "
"`0` can be used to `-J` to only list processes running on the host "
"system. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=266286[r266286]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:274
msgid ""
"The man:top[1] utility has been updated to filter by man:jail[8] ID or name, "
"in followup to the man:ps[1] change in "
"`r265229`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=266287[r266287]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:276
msgid ""
"The Blowfish man:crypt[3] default format has been changed to "
"`$2b$`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=266818[r266818]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:278
msgid ""
"The default man:newsyslog.conf[5] now includes files in the "
"`/etc/newsyslog.conf.d/` and `/usr/local/etc/newsyslog.conf.d/` directories "
"by default for "
"man:newsyslog[8]. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=267114[r267114]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:280
msgid ""
"A new flag, \"onifconsole\" has been added to `/etc/ttys`. This allows the "
"system to provide a login prompt via serial console if the device is an "
"active kernel console, otherwise it is equivalent to "
"`off`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=267243[r267243]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:282
msgid ""
"The man:arc4random[3] library has been updated to match that of "
"FreeBSD-CURRENT. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=267379[r267379]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:284
msgid ""
"The man:pmcstat[8] utility has been updated to include a new flag, `-l`, "
"which ends event collection after the specified number of "
"seconds. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=267411[r267411]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:286
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Project has migrated from the GNATS bug tracking system to "
"Bugzilla. The man:send-pr[1] utility used for submitting problem reports has "
"been replaced with a stub shell script that instructs to use the Bugzilla "
"web "
"interface. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=267911[r267911]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "man:periodic[8] Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:291
msgid ""
"The `/etc/periodic/security/800.loginfail` man:periodic[8] script has been "
"refined to catch more authentication failures and reduce false "
"positives. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=263662[r263662]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:293
#, no-wrap
msgid "man:rc[8] Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:296
msgid ""
"Support for \"first boot\" scripts has been added to man:rc[8]. See "
"man:rc[8] and man:rc.conf[5] for implementation "
"details. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=256917[r256917]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: website/content/en/releases/9.3R/relnotes.adoc:298
msgid ""
"The man:rc[8] system will now re-source man:rc.conf[5] on receipt of "
"`SIGALRM`. "
"http://svn.freebsd.org/viewvc/base?view=revision&revision=260432[r260432]"
msgstr ""

